Class method declarations
Class method declarations must not use a semicolon to separate individual
method declarations:
class Foo {
  doThing() {
    console.log("A");
  }
}

class Foo {
  doThing() {
    console.log("A");
  }; // <-- unnecessary
}

Method declarations should be separated from surrounding code by a single blank
line:
class Foo {
  doThing() {
    console.log("A");
  }

  getOtherThing(): number {
    return 4;
  }
}
